Mayan cenotes are natural sinkholes found in Mexico's Yucatán Peninsula, revered by the ancient Maya as sacred gateways to the underworld. Formed by limestone collapse, these crystal-clear pools were sources of water and sites for rituals.... and also, maybe the perfect campsite?
